{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, the hBN substrate affect the orbital magnetism in TBG [12].",
    "Samples in which the hBN is aligned with the TBG can exhibit an anomalous Hall effect at ν = +3 [21], an observation sharpened by later experiments that revealed a quantized Hall response at this filling [20].",
    "In such an aligned configuration, the coupling between the substrate and the TBG is enhanced.",
    "The substrate breaks Ĉ2z symmetry, and leads to the formation of Chern bands with C = ±1 if the coupling is modelled by a sublattice mass ∆σ z.",
    "In this regime, in consonance with the strong-coupling analysis in the absence of a substrate, interactions spontaneously break time-reversal symmetry, leading to a spin and valley polarized QAH state [30,31,62]."
  ]
}